# Premium Features: Use the Premium Folder

Any **premium (pro)** feature in this project must be built under `internal/premium/`, not in the shared/community tree.

## Where to Put What

| What | Location |
|------|----------|
| Premium engines (session, alert, report) | `internal/premium/<feature>/` (e.g. `internal/premium/session/engine.go`) |
| Premium repositories (pro-only CRUD) | `internal/premium/repository/` |
| Premium handlers | `internal/premium/<feature>/handler.go` |
| Premium services / utils stubs or impls | `internal/premium/service/`, `internal/premium/utils/` |

## Rules

- **Engines, handlers, and pro-only repos** for Session, Alert, Report (and any future premium feature) live under `internal/premium/`.
- **Shared code** (models, migrations, community repos, engine *interfaces*) stays in `internal/models`, `internal/repository`, `internal/engine` — only the **implementations** that are pro-only go in `internal/premium/`.
- All premium Go files must use `//go:build pro` so they compile only when building with `-tags pro`.
- Wire premium routes and dependencies in `internal/api/provider_pro.go`; keep `internal/api/provider_community.go` as a no-op for community builds.

## Examples

```go
// ✅ GOOD: premium session engine in premium folder
// File: internal/premium/session/engine.go
//go:build pro
package session
```

```go
// ✅ GOOD: premium-only repository in premium folder
// File: internal/premium/repository/credential_session_repository.go
//go:build pro
package repository
```

```go
// ❌ BAD: premium-only repository in community folder
// File: internal/repository/credential_session_repository.go  // do not add pro-only repos here
```
